answerText: Mount Aconcagua[10] Puncak Jaya is the highest point on the Australian continental plate. It belongs to this large island which is separated from Australia by the Torres strait, and is home to a country with capital Port Morseby.

question: Question: The Bermejo Pass lies to the south of this peak and a famous statue of Christ is located there.  [10] Identify this mountain, first scaled by Matthias Zurbriggen, whose namesake river empties into the Pacific north of Valparaiso.
